    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-03-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-03-03T11:00:00-05:00" n="617"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/3035: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-03T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1927—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Your No. 20, February 28, 5 p.m. Department agrees with you that for the
                    present you should continue your informal representations based on the
                    stipulations and spirit of Plan of Evacuation of 1922,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d617fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1922v02#pg_33">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1922, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 33</ref>.</note> Keep Department
                    informed by telegraph of future developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
